en: It's been shut down for years...

de: Ich kann diesen Gegenstand nicht tauschen.

en: Before The Shutdown these scientists were creating robots to defend the laboratory from intruders. When the robots turned on them they had to use whatever they could get to make new robots.

These guys were the janitors of the laboratory. They were generally hated by the scientists for getting in their way, so they gave them a weapon that reqiured them to stand in place in hopes of them killing themselves. (The lab needed tons of janitors, I swear)
Has a cool shotgun. Nothing else. (They're just so cool)

Really likes to work out. They have a big ego and are the leaders of the Gnome Resistence. They ALL really want to wear their unicorn underpants (Superstar Brand) in public but it's "unprofessional" and "socially unacceptable."
These gnomes usually have their big noses stuck in books instead of the real world - they are generally disrespected. If you're not careful they'll turn you into a slug.
The younger generation of the Gnomes. They don't have the strength to be buff, or the will to be wizards. So they use guns.
First entry in the DM series. Had to be locked in a cage as they sometimes broke lights.
The third model in the DM series. Less prone to breaking lights, as the scientists added special code to prevent that, but still had to be locked up because of constant misfires.
The second model in the DM Series. Was never released to the public since it was too ugly to be marketable.
Created to explore dangerous planets, modified to be slightly less mobile in an indoors enviroment. They would climb up on desks and kock things off.

Built by Hank as durable defenses against intruders. Originally there was only a single one made, but after The Shutdown they were duplicated. Was previously the H.A.N.K. model, but renamed to the H.A.N.K. Mini after the creation of H.A.N.K. Rumor has it that Hank was working on a H.A.N.K. Mini Pro before he died.

NOTE: Mr. Stick wishes to remain anonymous, so his real name will not be given (Ever). Mr. Stick was the one who started the Gnome Revolution against Jerry, as he was mistakenly given free will when he was created. The Gnome Revolution stands for liberty amongst Gnomes, and that everyone leaves them alone. Also, he's dyslexic. Totally irrelevant. (/H/i/s/ /n/a/m/e/ /i/s/ /J/h/o/n/ /S/t/i/c/k/)
Hank was into robotics. His most valued creation was the H.A.N.K. model. It would only make sense that Jerry name H.A.N.K. after H.A.N.K. Hank's least favorite food was lemons BTW.
